    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Alutiiq people, an indigenous people of Kodiak Island and surrounding areas. The Alutiiq are sometimes called called 'Aleut'; however, although related, this is distinguished from the general term 'Aleut,' which can be used to refer to a broader group of indigenous people whose territory is the Aleutian Islands.</Note_Text>
